Today I focused on understanding the fundamentals of DAX within Excel Power Pivot.

I explored the difference between calculated columns (row context) and measures (filter context), and how DAX calculations operate inside a relational data model rather than referencing fixed cell ranges like traditional Excel formulas.

Measures Created:
	•	Total Profit = SUM([Profit])
	•	Total Sales = SUM([Sale Price])
	•	Profit Margin % = DIVIDE([Total Profit], [Total Sales])